SQL_STMT_U.val: select TACO_ID, TACO_BANKCOUNTRY from :1/TACO where TACO_HUSR_ID = ':2' and TACO_OK = 'Y' and TACO_TYPE = 1 and case when TACO_BANKCOUNTRY = 'BE' then (select count(*) from :1/TACI where TACI_TACO_ID = TACO_ID) else (select count(*) from :1/TACI where TACI_TACO_ID = TACO_ID) end > case when TACO_BANKCOUNTRY = 'BE' then 2 else 9 end for fetch only

Text.val: -- If TACO_TOTAMOUNT of the old TACO row becomes <= 0, then the current split
has to be rolled back (undo)
-- Undo the whole split of one auto collection row because of credit notes,
TACO_AMOUNT of one of the new TACO rows or current TACO row <=0

selected TACO row has <= (TACO_BANKCOUNTRY <> 'BE',9,2) invoices
-- If TACO_TOTAMOUNT of the new TACO row <= 0, then the current split has to be
rolled back (undo), see T.S.
